Failure is always seen as a bad thing, but it’s actually the best way to grow and keep learning.

I’ve learned my biggest lessons from failure. It’s something that allows you to better yourself for next time so you don’t make the same mistakes.

That said, what lessons have you learned from failure?

#lessonslearned #failure #growthmindset

There’s some things in life you should just know not to do... for example, putting yourself in a position where a world heavyweight champion thinks you’re disrespecting him!!

This one is a story for the ages and I swear, my chest still hurts to this day 😂

To hear more of this story and what happened the next time I ran into Mike, check the link in my bio to listen to my @Audible Original Founding FUBU.

node.title: The Time I Almost Fought Mike Tyson

I got to sit down with all of the grant winners from @blackentrepreneursday and we talked about the struggles black business owners face, from funding to a general lack of equal opportunity. 

Although things have definitely begun to shift, we still have a long way to go until black and minority small business owners are given the same chance as everyone else.

Tag a black-owned small business below to give them some love.

I get this question ALL the time, and the answer is quite simple: I tune out everyone else at the start of my day and focus on what I need to do and what I want to accomplish for the day, week, etc. 

It’s about setting time to put yourself first before allowing others to invade you with their problems.

You may have heard of big business names such as Boeing, Ford and DuPont, but do you know the story behind these iconic brands?

This Memorial Day, check out @History Channel’s 3-night series #TitansThatBuiltAmerica. Not only will you find out what it takes to be a Titan in business, but you might even see a few cameos from me!

To the graduating class of 2021, here’s my advice to you all.

I hope you all give yourselves a huge pat on the back. You’ve made it through not only one of the most demanding times of your life, but continued to do so as the world was turned upside down.

Now, go out there and show us what you’re made of.

Tag a college grad you know that should watch this 🙏🏾

node.text:
Hmmmm… I’m not sure if I fully agree with this video. Money is absolutely a great tool that can be used for the greater good. There are so many amazing people that donate their money to organizations and people that save lives and the planet.
However, Gandhi, MLK, Mother Theresa, School Teachers, first responders, nurses and so many others have changed the world with little to no money as well.
Can you imagine how much worse this world would be if the everyday heroes used the excuse that they cant help because they don’t have any money??
Anyway, that’s my thoughts on this video. 
Maybe I’m wrong, maybe I’m right. What do you think?

Video repost: @therealnoreaga

I came across this amazing work of art and thought about how we often create our own mental boundaries.
Many don’t realize that before anything is ever created, built or accomplished, it must first be visualized. 
So take a moment and visualize what you will create, build or accomplish.  It all starts with that simple step. 
If you can’t see it you doing it, then why should anyone else?
If you already have the answer, feel free to speak it into the universe. I’m all ears!

Edit: @im_danny_from_miami 
#visualization 
#VisualizeAlbum
@fatmanscoop 
#Visualizetrack
